against both north and south.

00:20:21.620 --> 00:20:24.890 position:75%
Now, what does this mean for returning veterans?

00:20:24.890 --> 00:20:26.630
Well, there's a couple of issues.

00:20:26.630 --> 00:20:29.240
One, Black veterans were
targeted for violence in parts

00:20:29.240 --> 00:20:34.650 position:69%
of the country particularly the south
particularly if they were in their uniforms.

00:20:34.650 --> 00:20:37.090
This is one of the things
that leads the NAACP to engage

00:20:37.090 --> 00:20:40.440 position:67%
in a anti-lynching campaign during the 20s.

00:20:40.440 --> 00:20:47.160 position:66%
The NAACP itself will increase 6 fold
from roughly like 9,000 members to 63,000.

00:20:47.160 --> 00:20:51.050
Many of the AF Black veterans
will join the NAACP

00:20:51.050 --> 00:20:55.710 position:69%
and become Civil Rights activists
themselves besides Charles Hamilton Houston.

00:20:55.710 --> 00:21:02.350 position:66%
There are other examples such as Louis T.
Wright a famous doctor who served overseas

00:21:02.350 --> 00:21:05.000
and comes back and works for
the League for Democracy.

00:21:05.000 --> 00:21:07.600 position:72%
Othello McCain another one, Aiken August Pope.

00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:14.130 position:64%
These are just 3 other men who came back
