makes the arguments for Brown v. Board

00:22:57.010 --> 00:23:00.170 position:59%
in front of the Supreme Court in 1954.

00:23:00.170 --> 00:23:01.840 position:61%
So, it kind of comes full circle there.

00:23:01.840 --> 00:23:05.880 position:73%
And that's just some of the ways that World War
I affected not only Charles Hamilton Houston

00:23:05.880 --> 00:23:08.220 position:66%
but the larger African American community
and the Civil Rights movement to the NAACP

00:23:08.220 --> 00:23:10.410 position:67%
to the movement of African American peoples
from the south to the north and west

00:23:10.410 --> 00:23:13.350 position:67%
and to the changes in laws that eventually
culminated in Brown v. Board of Ed in 1954.

